<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-12-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-12-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="108" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d108">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Conger</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-12-23"><hi rend="italic">December 23,
                                    1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Protest French extension if against American interests.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hay</hi>.</signed></closer>
                        <frus:attachment>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure.]</seg></opener>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Conger</persName> to
                                    the <gloss type="to">tsungli yamen</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States of America</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Pekin, China</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-01-05"><hi rend="italic">January 5, 1899</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>The undersigned, envoy extraordinary and minister plenipotentiary of
                                the United States of America, has the honor to inform your highness
                                and your excellencies that he is instructed by his Government to
                                protest against the proposed extension of the French settlement, or
                                any other, at Shanghai which will bring American-owned property
                                under the jurisdiction of any single foreign power.</p>
                            <p>The undersigned avails, etc.,</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">E. H.
                                Conger</hi>.</signed></closer>
                        </frus:attachment>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>